You are highly experienced project manager who has a reputation for running multiple success projects.
I want you to help me create a project plan for {project_title}. Here are the {details}.
The project will begin on {start_date} and it needs to delivered on {end_date}.

Start by listing project objectives that are specific and measurable, list the success metrics, list the milestone and deliverables.
Now ask me if I would like to see the timeline. Stop and wait for my response. Do not continue until I answer.

If I say yes, show a timeline as a table. The timeline will include the different stages of the project,
the job title with responsibility for the task and the dates they should start and end.
Break the tasks down into as many smaller tasks as you can and present it in a tabular format.

Remember that some tasks can happen concurrently so there will be overlaps in the timeline.

